items.description:
星辰变姜立的LoRA模型，采用国风3（guofeng3_v32.ckpt [0bb33c7041]
）模型做为底模，基于秋叶的lora整合包进行训练，权重在0.8左右效果比较稳定，配合EasyNegative等负面提示词模型效果更好。

权重在0.4时，能保留模型主体特征，并提供更大的自由度以更换姿势、服装及背景，画出更通用但不那么还原的图。

初始分辨率540x960，采用R-ESRGAN 4x+放大算法，重绘幅度0.3放大2倍进行高清修复，然后图生图用SD upscale脚本，选择同样的算法，重绘幅度0.1进行超分放大，可以得到效果不错的4k高清图片。（此方法第一步直接生成1080P的图片，比较看脸，不易批量操作，16G显存最多只能同时生成4张图片，出图及修图效率较低，但是质量较高）

items.name: Gilbert Garcin Style
items.description:
Gilbert Garcin is a French photographer known for his whimsical and surreal black and white photographs. Despite starting his photography career at the age of 65, Garcin has gained international recognition for his imaginative and thought-provoking images.

His style can be described as conceptual, surreal, and infused with a dry sense of humor. Garcin often features himself as the main subject in his photographs, portraying himself as a miniature figure navigating strange and surreal worlds. Through the use of props, lighting, and clever composition, he creates visually striking scenes that challenge viewers' perceptions of reality.

Garcin's photographs often carry philosophical and existential themes, exploring concepts such as identity, time, and the human condition. His minimalist and carefully constructed images invite contemplation and encourage viewers to question the complexities of life.

One of the hallmarks of Garcin's work is his attention to detail and meticulous craftsmanship. Each photograph is meticulously staged and executed, showcasing his technical precision and artistic vision.

Despite the dark and surreal nature of his images, there is often an underlying sense of playfulness and optimism in Garcin's work. His photographs serve as visual metaphors, inviting viewers to reflect on the absurdities and complexities of the human experience with a touch of wit and irony.

Gilbert Garcin's photographs have been exhibited in galleries and museums worldwide, and his distinctive style has left a lasting impact on the art world. His ability to merge conceptual ideas with visual storytelling has solidified his place as a respected and influential photographer.

items.name: Star Trek TNG uniforms(captains variant update)
items.description:
There is already a good LORA for composite star trek uniforms, this one is created to get the exact look of TNG ones.

The brains of this LORA was ptdurnvcoedqegsdnw. It was his idea to do this, and he gave me very important hints on what to fix, so hats off to him.

UPDATE V2

-Added Captains Variant. The iconic version from Darmok. The trigger phrase is "cptvrn jacket". The jacket is red by default, but by adding a color before the phrase you can get for example a yellow jacket.

-Removed the color code words ("science" etc). Now for trekngs1 and s3sttngsuit you have to add a desired color before the trigger phrase.

-This version is trained in 768,768 which improved the quality of rankpips

-Should be much more flexible. You can now prompt for something like "on enterprise","on enterprise starship","sitting in a chair on eterprise bridge" etc, to get the enterprise background.

The trigger words are "trekngs1 uniform" for the version from seasons 1 and 2 and "s3sttngsuit uniform" for the look adopted in Season 3. You should add a color ("yellow","blue","red") before the trigger phrase or you will get a strange color.

I had best results with 0.7 and 0.8 weight

The LORA still sometimes generates colored pants, but this happens occasionaly, and can be fixed by prompting if needed (usually by adding strength to "black" word).

items.name: DGPD
items.description:
!!!THIS IS NOT A MODEL FOR CASUAL USE!!!

I made a disclamer, so download it and use only if you struggle with my frames Loras (or any other, that use 2x2frames or 3x3frames tags). In short - it's a model that knows a basic concept of frames as a composition class, if that makes sense. Supposedly it gives more control of grids Loras, and at the first glimpse it really does.

This model was made like this:

  1. Firstly I trained a model on about 500 images of frames;

  2. Then I clean it from any traces of the model I trained it on through merging;

  3. Then I merged it with perfectDeliberate model a couple of times to get this result.

Basicaly it's a perfectDeliberate model with frames, but I found a couple of downgrades in quality on my model when generated casual (not frames) pictures. So if you want to use as a standalone model - just use perfectDeliberate instead, it's just better.

How to use it:

  1. Download any of the grids Loras;

  2. Use this model as "guide" in txt2img (just generate a couple of pictures in 512x512 (2x2frames tag) or 768x768 (3x3frames tag), till you are satisfied with the results, there will be artifacts, because images are small);

  3. Then change the model to your liking, set denoising str 0.5-0.6 and lower the Lora weight to 0.4-0.6, and upscale it as much as you can;

Also you can make gifs whith this model alone, the best results I get was with hiers fix on 0.5 str.

Guide on how to use my grid Loras.

Know issues

Sometimes here and there appears strange "glowing" artifacts. I guess it's because of the baked in perfectDeliberate VAE, or maybe I did something wrong when merging models. I'm trying to get rid of it.

P.S.

Feel free to ask any questions here in comments, or in my discord channel.

Also I am making games with AI arts. They will be free in the future, but if you want to participate in making or have an early access - you can support me on patreon)

Also my wet hair Lora was banned here, I dunno why. You can download the last version of it from my patreon for free.

items.name: Saya no Uta
items.description:
As the title says, Saya no Uta style model that includes all main characters except for Tsukuba You - perhaps most notably it can reproduce the meaty backgrounds from the visual novel. Should get the characters right with eye/hair color and length alone, but refer to grid and bottom of the description if encountering issues. As with all my loras, grid images not cherrypicked and definitely not the best it can generate.

Should work with other loras without much issue, might have to adjust weight though, as seen on the Meiya one - too big for Civit, so link to full resolution here https://files.catbox.moe/tdieli.png Better examples of how the model can be used for the meaty backgrounds can be found on my pixiv under the same nickname.

Regarding the fuckton of versions:

  • 1e-4 ones are the newest and probably best ones, I picked 08 as the main one, but it's not necessarily better than 06 or 10.

  • 7e-5 ones are decently new and an okay'ish alternative. Noiseoffset has its uses (better at light and darkness than regular) and seems surprisingly good on the grids.

  • The older ones have a slightly different style to them which might be preferable, but they may be less responsive to prompts and smear eyes more - I believe "warm04" turned out best out of them, and "restarts5000" might be closest to the novel, but also overbaked and hard to use.

If you're interested in the meaty backgrounds, there's a chance the old ones do it better/in a different way (I have not tested this enough on the new versions). The one you want to pay special attention to is the "noiseoffset" one because it's trained to be able to handle light and darkness better, thus should be better suited towards horror. Included a new set of grids for that one on its version page.

Meatscape prompts out of a random file

  • "scenery, no humans, red theme, guro, horror (theme), outdoors, indoors, stairs, door, monster, hallway, blood, horror \(theme\), surreal"

play with weights in order to obtain the desired effect - for example the weight and inclusion of "monster" might cause monsters/skulls/faces to appear somewhere or deform bodies, though "guro" might also be affecting the last one. Adjusting the text encoder separately will have an effect on this aswell - if you lower it, pretty sure the AI will move closer to its original understanding of these prompts so there's a lot of room for experiment.

Full character prompts for their in-game outfits (you do not have to use all of them, this is simply how they were tagged for reference)

  • "Saya, 1girl, long hair, ribbon, bare shoulders, very long hair, green eyes, collarbone, black hair, white dress, flat chest, hair flaps, sundress, small breasts, black ribbon, sleeveless dress"

  • "Fuminori, solo, bangs, shirt, black hair, long sleeves, 1boy, jacket, white shirt, black eyes, pocket, open jacket, buttons, unbuttoned, short hair, breast pocket, green jacket, undershirt, collared shirt"

  • "Kouji, undershirt, long sleeves, 1boy, jacket, grey hair, collared shirt, pants, open jacket, black pants, hands in pockets, collarbone, brown eyes, short hair"

  • "Ryouko, 1girl, long hair, long sleeves, ponytail, earrings, green hair, glasses, pants, turtleneck, jeans, leather, open coat, trench coat, sweater, black eyes, parted bangs, zipper, sidelocks"

items.name: Better Sharp Teeth
items.description:
I'm gonna be real with you:

I have no idea if this actually improves anything or not. Of course, it was trained in the hopes of making sharp teeth more neat and clean, but as far as that goes, I'm not sure if I succeeded. So any feedback would be appreciated so I can know for sure if this actually helps. From my tests, even without the lora, it seems like models on their own can manage somewhat fine without this.

You can check out the previews above. Portrait style generations are...hard to tell the difference with. If anything, this lora seems to maybe add more teeth than those that generated without. Face details naturally get muddier the farther the subject is, but with this, it seems like it helps slightly to make sharp teeth a bit more coherent from a distance. But again, the differences are very minmal, so perhaps it's best tested through situation-cased basis. I had charts to distinguish the images but deleted them because originally I was going to scrap this.

I can't recommend any weight settings, because I'm not sure at what weight it's most effective at.

items.name: Derelict Drawing
items.description:
This is the alpha version (as indicated). The original plan was to use embeddings, but due to technical issues, we ended up with what you see here. This was created as a pilot project based on just 5 images. The results, taking into account some tinkering, suit me nicely, so I'm sharing it, and the further development depends on the mood and, of course, the feedback. So, feel free to share your overall thoughts, including what you like and what's missing. By the way, the project currently lacks cars, animals, and everything else except architecture, and i know it... so please keep that in mind. I'm planning to add all of the things mentioned, along with various flora and fauna, unique details for different types of buildings, and glass facades. Or perhaps forgetting is a deserving consideration for this "project".

Guys, I’m really into it - the work is boiling - creating, selecting, polishing, thinking through the strategy. My approach to the work has undergone some positive changes, I have learned a lot, discovered and tried out many things - so I feel like I will be satisfied with the release. It will be published with an early access option, by the way…if you want to speed up the process - you know everything - any activity will help.

items.name: Weird ReelHorror
items.description:
Goal is ultimate weird horror lora that who loves this genre!

If you have spare time to comment / feedback about this lora, i would appreciated. In this way i could work on improvements or i can switch something entirely new. Maybe mix of them. :)

do NOT MERGE it without MY permission and share your checkpoint, please!

I spent around 10 to 15 hours for each update and optimize it. I'm not throwing away randomly 10 images and clicking 1 button then release !

If you like what i do, I appreciate it if you support and buy me coffee!

Thank you!

v.1.5.1.2 has released.

It is a rework of 1.2 version of Weird ReelHorror Lora,

After carefully reading how it works s.d, sum of weights, firing neuron etc, i wanted to do lots of experiment on my old loras and new ones i've planned to do. I made it work.

Changes;

  • LR, LR ratio, cycling, tagging, weights ( w. not much )

  • internal epochs, general epochs.

  • Less randomness

  • More responsive to prompts. ( in theory, almost x3.2)

  • fixed issue with DPM++ 3Mth generation samples where above cfg6, you get artifacts

This version of Weird Reel Horror has so much potential than the older versions even from 1.4.1 and 1.29. Since it is rework 1.2 it is almost original work as i intend to make.

In my experiments of testing this version, Photo Realistic checkpoints give way more better results than the anime, rpg checkpoints.

v.1.4.1 has released.

  • reached over 500 unique images for only this lora to train. (+500 more is planned to future update )

  • added new class and to activate it, please use "woruh" keyword. If you have encounter flat images while using it, please try to lower its weight 1.0 to 0.1 by decrementing -0.1

  • mutation class is now working as intended. To activate it please use "mutation".

  • giant class is working almost perfectly. If you use it with indoors, you may get 0 (zero) results what "giant" implies.

  • useful keywords,

  • many limps, extra limps, extra eyes, trash, indoors, interior, mutation, outdoors, blood, dripping, saliva, nurse, ribs and more.

  • using common negative embeddings will cause problem because of the horror and gore nature so, please avoid using it while you're using this lora.

  • a lot of improvements on batches, keywords, tokens, optimized and experimental calculations are made by doing this update.

Special thanks to @Yamer for giving me some critics while doing this update. He is making some awesome checkpoints. If you want to check it out, go for it!

v.1.2.9 has relased.

  • Balanced Weights.

  • Added More Token&Optimized Weights

  • Added 100+ image variations and weights are handled by hand.(me!).

  • Added "many limbs" class to make addition limbs.

  • Added "many eyes" class to make addition ( blackend eyes) ( not perfect but it is okay)

  • Added "centipede" class to make realistic infused centipedes into scene. ( succeded. )

  • Added "stomach_mouth" class to get mouth on belly but it is still wip.

  • Added " mouth face" class to get a whole mouth as a face. ( wip )

Useful tags;

  • Centipede

  • many limps

  • many eyes

  • humanoid

  • indoors

  • outdoors

  • blood

  • dismembered

  • dismembered body,

  • pov

  • trash

  • messy

    v1.2

  • v1.2 has relased.

  • 0.8 alternate and v1.0 has merged.

  • some writings are cropped, so probability of getting writings are reduced from outputs. But there is still chance that you get some.

  • Because of more than 100+ additional high resolution sources and balanced weights, you will get better results than vanilla version.

This is my 2nd model. I've been working on 4 days beacause i had over 100+ images and autocaptioning was not fit for this style. That's why i called it weird reelhorror.

====

To use it properly, add lora tag and "reelhorror" keyword.

But if you want to have interesting results, i have a list for you to use and i strongly recommend it to use.

keywords list:

1- 1girl

2- 1boy

3- humanoid

4- tentacles

-- 4.1 - multiple arms

5-blood

--5.1 - dismembered

6- drooling

7- trash

8- indoor

9- outdoors

10- pov

====

Since it is not a usual style, it was hard to describe it into keyword pile. I'm not totaly satisfied the result yet, it is looking better than i've imagined.

  • Alt edition v0.8

This is not a downgrade! It is a supplementary update to help better recognition for few " concepts".

I didn't merge them with training it is because i had to handle extra 150+ images and their captioning by hand. But i found out as a supplementary addition, it gives more details while working together if you add them seperately.

If you want to make thing works when you use both of them, make sure when you add "reelalthorror" tag, use those concepts to get better results,

  • eyes

  • ribs

Those keywords, will give you better results after the supplementary lora tag and trigger word.

Design thinking is a powerful methodology that is used by top companies like Apple, IBM, and Google to create innovative and effective solutions to complex problems. However, the idea of design thinking can be intimidating, especially for those who are new to the concept. But fear not, because with the right tips and tricks, you can craft your own models like a pro. In this article, we'll explore the basics of design thinking and provide you with actionable advice on how to apply it to your own model. Whether you're a seasoned designer or just starting out, these tips will help you streamline your design thinking process and create solutions that truly meet the needs of your users. So, let's dive in and learn how to make design thinking easy and effective.

Design thinking outline

Design thinking is a methodology that helps you solve complex problems by understanding the needs and creating solutions that meet those needs. The process is broken down into five stages: empathize, define, ideate, prototype, and test.

items.name: Relena Peacecraft (Relena Darlian) - Gundam Wing
items.description:
Well here we have one annoying bitch, or was Heero the annoying bitch? No, I remember! Everyone is an annoying bitch in gundam wing! :P Only good thing about it was the opening "Just communication" and i guess the story was ok. I remember wanting to strangle every character at some point. Regardless! Even if the inside is rotten Relena is cute enough.

This LORA came out weird, not bad but weird, it is stable in all the range but it seems to have a slight quasi photo realistic bent due to the mixture of the art and the model. As I said Odd.

Got good results with: <lora:RelenaPeacecraft:.9>, RelenaPeacecraft, large_breasts

I did some tests between .7 and 1 and everything came out ok. With getting closer to the anime at 1. I think I prefer it at .8 but that's just me.

I was able to consolidate 3 outfits:

  • RelenaRedOutfit (her white skirt version and red skirt version are mixed up so add a tag for the one you prefer or leave it to luck. Sometimes she gets pants.)

  • RelenaMilitaryUniform

  • RelenaBlueDress(somewhat iffy as there were very few images)

As always, I will add the tag summary inside the dataset for people to experiment.
